`newInstance`? Perhaps calling a public static method with a fixture could invoke the static initializer, but I'm curious if I really need to dynamically load the class or if I can just use a local one!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_5mxMymzM8WAs2d6JU0NwrgNw|fc_0a68fd46c0f7d7590169f540f42c548194917b454005e60e5d", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "metadata/ant/ant/1.6/reachability-metadata.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 450, "output": 3214, "cacheRead": 22016, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 25680, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777680584136, "responseId": "resp_0a68fd46c0f7d7590169f540c896a08194ab8828fba2b494db"}}
